  <entry>
    <title>Chelsea News 230220</title>
    <url>/2023/02/20/Chelsea-News-230220/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<!-- -->

<h2 id="Chelsea-given-two-days-off-training-as-pressure-ramps-up-on-Graham-Potter"><a href="#Chelsea-given-two-days-off-training-as-pressure-ramps-up-on-Graham-Potter" class="headerlink" title="Chelsea given two days off training as pressure ramps up on Graham Potter"></a>Chelsea given two days off training as pressure ramps up on Graham Potter</h2><p>ramp up : 增加</p>
<p>two days off : 两个休息日</p>
<figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">由于Graham Potter压力的增加，切尔西给了两天的休息时间</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<p>According to most media reports over the weekend, Chelsea are still backing manager Graham Potter despite losing to bottom of the table Southampton on Saturday afternoon.</p>
<p>back : 支持</p>
<figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">根据这周末大多数媒体的报道，尽管切尔西在周六下午输给了榜尾的南安普顿，切尔西仍然支持主教练Graham Potter。</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<p>Chelsea fans are used to the club sacking managers after poor runs like Potter has been having, but we have always been hearing that Potter is the long-term project manager under this ownership group. But that is going to be tested now and over the next few weeks for sure.</p>
<figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">切尔西的球迷们已经习惯了俱乐部在一连串糟糕的比赛表现后（比如Potter近期的表现）解雇主教练，但我们一直听说现在的管理层将波特视作球队长期计划的教练。这毫无疑问会在当下和未来几周的时间里受到检验。</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<p>The pressure is fully on Potter right now regardless, and you’d be silly to bet against the Chelsea board sacking him.</p>
<p>bet against : 打赌某事不会发生</p>
<figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">不管如何，压力现在全部到了Potter身上，你也不会蠢到去打赌切尔西的董事会不会解雇他</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<p>Speculation and rumours have continued this week after Chelsea have been given two days off training, although these days are apparently scheduled days off regardless. Even still, this will certainly add fuel to the sacking fire and get tongues wagging.</p>
<p>rumour : 谣言</p>
<p>tongue : 舌头</p>
<p> tongue wag : 说闲话</p>
<p>even still : 即便如此</p>
<figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">在切尔西给了两天的休息日之后，猜测和谣言一直在持续，尽管这两个休息日显然是日程表的安排。即便如此，这难免会有很多议论，也会为解雇风波添一把火。</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<p>Many Blues fans are now fuming that the players have been rewarded with two days off after such poor form of late.</p>
<figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">蓝军球迷现在非常不高兴，因为球员们在最近如此糟糕的比赛表现后，还得到了两天的休息日。</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

]]></content>
